Program: Discovery
Title: Ageing - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx79
Last Broadcast Date: 25 September 1998
The second of a two-part examination of the ageing process. Presenter John Newell examines the ageing process and how the advancement of society has meant we are living longer than any previous generation. The programme looks at why different species have different lifespans.